## Code Example Standards

### Rule: Always Provide Complete, Runnable Examples

✅ **DO - Complete Example:**
```javascript
const Refold = require('@refold/sdk');

const refold = new Refold({
  apiKey: process.env.REFOLD_API_KEY
});

async function syncPurchaseOrders() {
  try {
    const result = await refold.workflows.execute({
      workflowId: 'wf_sap_po_sync',
      linkedAccountId: 'la_acme_corp',
      data: {
        company_codes: ['1000', '2000'],
        status: 'Approved'
      }
    });
    
    console.log(`Synced ${result.records_processed} purchase orders`);
    return result;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Sync failed:', error.message);
    throw error;
  }
}

syncPurchaseOrders();
```

❌ **DON'T - Partial Snippet:**
```javascript
// Just call the execute method
refold.workflows.execute(...)
```

### Code Languages Priority

1. **JavaScript** (Node.js) - Primary
2. **cURL** - Secondary (always include for API endpoints)
3. **Python** - When relevant for data/ML use cases

### cURL Example Format

```bash
curl -X POST https://api.refold.ai/v2/workflows/execute \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "workflow_id": "wf_sap_po_sync",
    "linked_account_id": "la_acme_corp",
    "data": {
      "company_codes": ["1000", "2000"],
      "status": "Approved"
    }
  }'
```

