## Common Mistakes to Avoid

| Mistake | Correct Approach |
|---------|------------------|
| Partial code snippets | Always show complete, runnable code |
| Passive voice | Use active voice ("Create a workflow" not "A workflow can be created") |
| Jargon without definition | Define technical terms or link to Terminology page |
| Missing error handling | Show try/catch and error scenarios in examples |
| Outdated screenshots | Ensure images match current UI exactly |
| Dead links | Verify all internal and external links before commit |
| Inconsistent naming | Use exact field names as they appear in UI |
| Salesforce examples | Use SAP/NetSuite/Tipalti for enterprise scenarios |
| Missing "What's Next" | Every page needs navigation to related content |
| Fluff words | Remove "just", "easily", "simply", "obviously", "very" |
| Long paragraphs | Keep to 3-4 sentences max per paragraph |
| Complex sentences | One idea per sentence |

